They wanted their voices to be heard so they hijacked an excavator and dug up the road. Residents of Sarafina in North West took the streets in a service delivery problem on Monday. The road in an entrance into their kasi. Video was tweeted by Yusuf Abramjee with the caption: "Protestors destroy road at Sarafina entrance next to N12 yesterday afternoon. They hijacked an excavator and started to break up the road between Klerksdorp and Potchefstroom." People on social media were angered by the video.  